The 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference, hosted in partnership with Liquid Telecom, took place at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand on 6 June 2019. The event is a meeting place for the South African IT community and a platform for IT decision makers to interact and do business with South Africa’s top cloud and hosting providers. The 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference attracted over 1,100 ICT executives and managers from across South Africa and neighbouring countries. These delegates were treated to excellent presentations from South Africa’s top cloud, hosting, and security experts. Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou was the emcee at the event, with Liquid Telecom’s new CEO Reshaad Sha delivering the keynote address. The expo area hosted South Africa’s top cloud and hosting players, which included Liquid Telecom, Huawei, Connection Telecom, VMWare, Teraco, Schneider Electric, Axis, and Microsoft. Photos of the great event are posted below.                               